# REQUIREMENTS:
1.SERVER-1(ubuntu)
2.install docker

### steps to execute:
# step1:
launch ec2 with t2 micro
connect to ec2 instance
sudo apt-get update

# step2:
1.Install Docker
(sudo apt-get install docker.io)

2.Start Docker
sudo systemctl start docker

3.Enable Docker to start at boot
sudo systemctl enable docker

4.Verify Docker installation
sudo docker --version

5.check the status of docker
sudo systemctl status docker

# step3:
clone the code from git hub

goto nginxweb-with-docker 

ste4:
Build the Docker Image && Run the Docker Container
(sudo docker build -t sagar .)
(sudo docker run -d -p 80:80 sagar)

step5:
Access the application from your web browser
1.Ensure your server's firewall allows HTTP traffic(port 80 should be allow)
2.hit public IP address with 80(publicip:80)

